cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new method that integrates feature extraction, response map generation, and model update into a neural network, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses residual learning to take appearance changes into account, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics).
